[Predictions]

@Goat******76 I agree with your take bar from the fact that you're disregarding Aaron Picos submission win against Aiden Lee, sure his record is rough but Aiden Lee does not suck lol he's a very crafty vet and he has been on a roll recently.

He's also fought tough opponents practically his whole career and has pretty good wins over fighters like Ludovit Klein, Lee is nasty on the ground majority of his losses came from SD and some Knockouts but subbing him is no joke at all its very impressive.

[Predictions]

@The Duck he doesn't deserve the credit for his win against Pantoja, but he does deserve the recognition as a champion despite the result, and the sheer fact that he's so active at such a young age and that 5 months before he had a 3 round war against the #1 contender at the time where they threw 200 significant strikes each is mindblowing.

* Edited at 04.01.2026,  4:25 AM ET *

[Predictions]

@McFarlanders first of all there was no dirty move. It's no one's fault for what happened to Pantoja. Those things sometimes happen, and this time Pantoja was unlucky it had to happen to him. Going life and death with Royval doesn't mean he's not a very high level fighter, he clearly won that fight, but doesn't happen to have the KO power that Kape has, hence he wasn't able to KO Royval even though he hurt him multiple times throughout the fight and also dropped him in the last round. As you can see by my pfp I'm a major Manel Kape believer and I think he's the best 125er on the planet right now, but trying to undermine Joshua Van is a ******** move, even for an obvious ragebaiter like you.

* Edited at 04.01.2026,  7:03 AM ET *

[Predictions]

@flavorpacket Remember Blaydes vs Kuniev, when Kuniev was making his UFC debut. That fight got scrapped twice, and they were so adamant on making it happen, I found it fishy and thought they had to have a reason for it. Later we learnt Blaydes was ill, had injury issues and later tore his MCL during the fight. Maybe, just maybe, Curtis Blaydes is on a big physical decline and has certain health issues that the UFC know about, and they see that as the ideal chance to remove him from contention at 265, and at the same time put Josh Hokit into the title mix asap.

* Edited at 04.02.2026,  3:00 AM ET *

[Predictions]

@B7L7 good catch on blaydes having some injury issues over the last year or so, i did forget about that. he has a ton of mma mileage at 35 so i guess that's both good and bad. i completely agree the ufc would like to get blaydes out of contention and bring hokit into the mix. so how do you think hokit gets it done? i still have a hard time seeing hokit steamroll blaydes just because gimenis and freeman are both relatively green so it's hard for me to get a read on how hokit will perform against someone with 20 ufc fights (with many of those fights being against top ranked guys).

* Edited at 04.02.2026,  4:26 PM ET *
